  "takeaway_brief": "MyLife.com used deceptive teaser results suggesting searched individuals had criminal or sex offender records to sell subscriptions, and made cancellation deliberately difficult.",
  "takeaway_full": "MyLife.com and its CEO sold background report subscriptions by displaying deceptive search result teasers falsely implying that individuals had criminal or sex offender records when they did not, failed to clearly disclose subscription terms and automatic renewal, made cancellation extremely difficult, and furnished consumer reports without permissible purpose in violation of the FCRA. The FTC required MyLife to implement an FCRA compliance program, cease prohibited and deceptive practices, ban negative option billing, pay monetary judgments, provide annual certifications, and comply with acknowledgment, compliance reporting, recordkeeping, and monitoring requirements."
}